info.report-description: LTE Cell Load measurement (M8001) measures packet scheduling related measurements.

kpi_info.title: period_duration (period_duration)
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: PDCP_SDU_DELAY_DL_DTCH_MIN (M8001C0)
kpi_info.use: The minimum retention period for a PDCP SDU (DL) inside the eNB. UPDATED: At the first transmission of a TB containing a segment of the SDU.

kpi_info.title: PDCP_SDU_DELAY_DL_DTCH_MAX (M8001C1)
kpi_info.use: The maximum retention period for a PDCP SDU (DL) inside the eNB. UPDATED: At the first transmission of a TB containing a segment of the SDU.

kpi_info.title: PDCP_SDU_DELAY_DL_DTCH_MEAN (M8001C2)
kpi_info.use: The mean retention period for a PDCP SDU (DL) inside the eNB. UPDATED: At the first transmission of a TB containing a segment of the SDU.

kpi_info.title: PDCP_SDU_DELAY_UL_DTCH_MIN (M8001C3)
kpi_info.use: The minimum retention period for a PDCP SDU (UL) inside the eNB. UPDATED: The counter is updated if the current minimum is greater than the last detected delay value at the transmission of the SDU via S1 interface.

kpi_info.title: PDCP_SDU_DELAY_UL_DTCH_MAX (M8001C4)
kpi_info.use: The maximum retention period for a PDCP SDU (UL) inside the eNB. UPDATED: The counter is updated if the current maximum is less than the last detected delay value at the transmission of the SDU via S1 interface.

kpi_info.title: PDCP_SDU_DELAY_UL_DTCH_MEAN (M8001C5)
kpi_info.use: The mean retention period for a PDCP SDU (UL) inside the eNB. UPDATED: The counter is updated based on currently calculated mean delay value at the transmission of the SDU via S1 interface.

kpi_info.title: RACH_STP_ATT_SMALL_MSG (M8001C6)
kpi_info.use: The number of RACH setup attempts for small size messages (only contention based). UPDATED: The reception of an RA preamble group A sent by the UE to the eNB.

kpi_info.title: RACH_STP_ATT_LARGE_MSG (M8001C7)
kpi_info.use: The number of RACH setup attempts for large size messages (only contention based). UPDATED: The reception of an RA preamble group B sent by the UE to the eNB.

kpi_info.title: RACH_STP_COMPLETIONS (M8001C8)
kpi_info.use: The number of RACH setup completions (contention based and dedicated preambles). UPDATED: The transmission of a RA preamble response sent by the eNB to the UE.

kpi_info.title: TRANSMIT_TB_ON_PCH (M8001C9)
kpi_info.use: The number of transmitted transport blocks on PCH. UPDATED: The transmission of a TB on PCH.

kpi_info.title: TRANSMIT_TB_ON_BCH (M8001C10)
kpi_info.use: The number of transmitted transport blocks on BCH. UPDATED: The transmission of a TB on BCH.

kpi_info.title: TRANSMIT_TB_ON_DL_SCH (M8001C11)
kpi_info.use: The number of transmitted transport blocks on DL-SCH. UPDATED: The transmission of a TB for the first time on DL-SCH.

kpi_info.title: HARQ_RETRANS_ON_DL_SCH (M8001C12)
kpi_info.use: The number of HARQ retransmissions on DL-SCH. UPDATED: HARQ retransmission of a TB on DL-SCH.

kpi_info.title: CORR_NON_DUPL_UL_SCH_TB (M8001C13)

kpi_info.title: UL_UE_DATA_BUFF_AVG (M8001C150)

This measurement can be used to monitor the congestion level of the eNB queuing system, realized by schedulers for the shared channels. kpi_info.title: UE_DRB_UL_DATA_QCI_1 (M8001C419)
kpi_info.use: The average number of UEs per TTI with buffered data in UL for logical channel group (LCG) which have VoIP (QCI1) bearer mapped. Note that this counter provides reliable results if only QCI1 is mapped into the LCG1. The reported value is 100 times higher than the actual value (for example 1.00 is stored as 100). UPDATED: The value is the arithmetical average of samples taken from the number of UEs with buffered data in UL for logical channel group which have VOIP (QCI1) bearer mapped. The samples are taken from each active TTI there is UL data scheduled at least for one UE.

kpi_info.title: UE_DRB_UL_DATA_NON_GBR (M8001C420)
kpi_info.use: The average number of UEs per TTI with buffered data in UL for logical channel groups which have non-GBR bearers (QCI5...9) mapped. Note that in case of mixed GBR/non-GBR bearers mapping into the LCG there can be an error in the obtained results because it cannot be distinguished whether this counter is updated only for non-GBR bearers or also for GBR bearers. The reported value is 100 times higher than the actual value (for example 1.00 is stored as 100). UPDATED: The value is the arithmetical average of samples taken from the number of UEs with buffered data in UL for logical channel groups with non-GBR (QCI5...9) bearer mapped. The samples are taken from each active TTI there is UL data scheduled at least for one UE.

kpi_info.title: CELL_LOAD_UNL_POW_RES (M8001C429)
kpi_info.use: This counter provides the average number of RRC connected UEs which have set the "deviceType" in the "UE-EUTRA-Capability" to "noBenFromBatConsumpOpt", that is which have indicated to the network (eNB) that they do not foresee to benefit from network-based battery consumption optimization (3GPP TS 36.331, TS 36.306), that is which have indicated that their power supply resources are not limited to the small battery of a normal UE (for example LTE smart phone with limited battery life) but that they have access to unlimited power supply resources (for example LTE USB-stick connected to a PC using the PC power supply resources). UPDATED: eNB-internal average calculation of the number of RRC connected UEs which have set the "deviceType" in the "UE-EUTRA-Capability" to "noBenFromBatConsumpOpt" (3GPP TS 36.331, TS 36.306); the average is calculated as the arithmetical average over the measurement period.

kpi_info.title: CA_DL_CAP_UE_AVG (M8001C494)
kpi_info.use: This counter provides the average number of DL CA-capable UEs in the current cell, which - in case of CA configuration - serves as PCell for these UEs. The reported value is 100 times higher than the actual value (for example 1.00 is stored as 100). UPDATED: The arithmetical average of samples taken from the number of DL CA-capable UEs.

kpi_info.title: CA_SCELL_CONF_UE_AVG (M8001C495)
kpi_info.use: This counter provides the average number of UEs in the current cell, which have a configured SCell. The reported value is 100 times higher than the actual value (for example 1.00 is stored as 100). UPDATED: The arithmetical average of samples taken from the number of UEs with a configured SCell.

kpi_info.title: CA_SCELL_ACTIVE_UE_AVG (M8001C496)
kpi_info.use: This counter provides the average number of UEs in the current cell, which have an activated SCell. The reported value is 100 times higher than the actual value (for example 1.00 is stored as 100). UPDATED: The arithmetical average of samples taken from the number of UEs with an activated SCell.

kpi_info.title: CA_DL_CAP_UE_3CC_AVG (M8001C497)
kpi_info.use: This counter provides the average number of DL CA-capable UEs for 3 component carriers (3 CCs) in the current cell. This cell (in case of CA configuration) serves as PCell for these UEs. The reported value is 100 times higher than the actual value (for example, 1.00 is stored as 100). Note: If a UE supports 2 CCs as well, this is counted in M8001C494. UPDATED: The counter is updated by the arithmetical average of samples taken from those UEs that are DL CA-capable for 3 component carriers.

kpi_info.title: CA_2SCELLS_CONF_UE_AVG (M8001C498)
kpi_info.use: This counter provides the average number of UEs in the current cell having two configured SCells.The reported value is 100 times higher than the actual value (for example, 1.00 is stored as 100). UPDATED: This counter is updated by the arithmetical average of samples taken from the number of UEs with two configured SCells.

kpi_info.title: CA_2SCELLS_ACTIVE_UE_AVG (M8001C499)
kpi_info.use: This counter provides the average number of UEs in the current cell, which have two activated SCells.The reported value is 100 times higher than the actual value (for example, 1.00 is stored as 100). UPDATED: The arithmetical average of samples taken from the number of UEs with two activated SCells.
